                    <msContents>
                        <summary> Fol. 1b. The epistle of Abba Salama on the Dogma of the Trinity --
                            Fol. 3a. The book of Enoch -- Fol. 45a. The book of Job -- 70b. Remarks
                            in Amharic: 1) On the weights "Talaq awaqi" and "Tanash awaqi" 2) On the
                            computation of the fast "Arba tom" -- Fol. 71a. The book of Daniel --
                            Fol. 87a. The book of Ezra -- Fol. 103a. An interpretation of the vision
                            of the eagle in Ezra 11-12. Fol. 104a. A religious song in 7 strophes.
                            The first three bear the heading "Wazema" (Dillmann Lex. s. v.: Modus
                            quidas cantandi hymnos ecclesiasticos"), the other 4 bear the heading
                            "Selasse" (Dillmann, Lex. s. v.: "Genus carminis ex ternionibus
                            constans"), the page is completed by a short prayer and the heading
                            "Mawadis zaekul som" </summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                            <locus from="3r">Fols 3r and following</locus>
                            <title>The book of Enoch</title>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                            <locus from="45r">Fols 45r and following</locus>
                            <title>The book of Job</title>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i3">
                            <locus from="71r">Fols 71r and following</locus>
                            <title>The book of Daniel</title>

                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i4">
                            <locus from="87r">Fols 87r and following</locus>
                            <title>The book of Ezra</title>
                        </msItem>

                        



